21// Helper method to get the sampler extracted struct type of a parameter.
22TType *GetStructSamplerParameterType(TSymbolTable *symbolTable, const TVariable &param)
23{
24 const TStructure *structure = param.getType().getStruct();
25 const TSymbol *structSymbol = symbolTable->findUserDefined(structure->name());
26 ASSERT(structSymbol && structSymbol->isStruct());
27 const TStructure *structVar = static_cast<const TStructure *>(structSymbol);
28 TType *structType = new TType(structVar, false);
29
30 if (param.getType().isArray())
31 {
32 structType->makeArrays(param.getType().getArraySizes());
33 }
34
35 ASSERT(!structType->isStructureContainingSamplers());
36
37 return structType;
38}
39
40TIntermSymbol *ReplaceTypeOfSymbolNode(TIntermSymbol *symbolNode, TSymbolTable *symbolTable)
41{
42 const TVariable &oldVariable = symbolNode->variable();
43
44 TType *newType = GetStructSamplerParameterType(symbolTable, oldVariable);
45
46 TVariable *newVariable =
47 new TVariable(oldVariable.uniqueId(), oldVariable.name(), oldVariable.symbolType(),
48 oldVariable.extension(), newType);
49 return new TIntermSymbol(newVariable);
50}
51
52TIntermTyped *ReplaceTypeOfTypedStructNode(TIntermTyped *argument, TSymbolTable *symbolTable)
53{
54 TIntermSymbol *asSymbol = argument->getAsSymbolNode();
55 if (asSymbol)
56 {
57 ASSERT(asSymbol->getType().getStruct());
58 return ReplaceTypeOfSymbolNode(asSymbol, symbolTable);
59 }
60
61 TIntermTyped *replacement = argument->deepCopy();
62 TIntermBinary *binary = replacement->getAsBinaryNode();
63 ASSERT(binary);
64
65 while (binary)
66 {
67 ASSERT(binary->getOp() == EOpIndexDirectStruct || binary->getOp() == EOpIndexDirect);
68
69 asSymbol = binary->getLeft()->getAsSymbolNode();
70
71 if (asSymbol)
72 {
73 ASSERT(asSymbol->getType().getStruct());
74 TIntermSymbol *newSymbol = ReplaceTypeOfSymbolNode(asSymbol, symbolTable);
75 binary->replaceChildNode(binary->getLeft(), newSymbol);
76 return replacement;
77 }
78
79 binary = binary->getLeft()->getAsBinaryNode();
80 }
81
82 UNREACHABLE();
83 return nullptr;
84}
85
86void GenerateArrayStrides(const std::vector<size_t> &arraySizes,
87 std::vector<size_t> *arrayStridesOut)
88{
89 auto &strides = *arrayStridesOut;
90
91 ASSERT(strides.empty());
92 strides.reserve(arraySizes.size() + 1);
93
94 size_t currentStride = 1;
95 strides.push_back(1);
96 for (auto it = arraySizes.rbegin(); it != arraySizes.rend(); ++it)
97 {
98 currentStride *= *it;
99 strides.push_back(currentStride);
100 }
101}
102
103// This returns an expression representing the correct index using the array
104// index operations in node.
105static TIntermTyped *GetIndexExpressionFromTypedNode(TIntermTyped *node,
106 const std::vector<size_t> &strides,
107 TIntermTyped *offset)
108{
109 TIntermTyped *result = offset;
110 TIntermTyped *currentNode = node;
111
112 auto it = strides.end();
113 --it;
114 // If this is being used as an argument, not all indices may be present;
115 // count how many indices are there.
116 while (currentNode->getAsBinaryNode())
117 {
118 TIntermBinary *asBinary = currentNode->getAsBinaryNode();
119
120 switch (asBinary->getOp())
121 {
122 case EOpIndexDirectStruct:
123 break;
124
125 case EOpIndexDirect:
126 case EOpIndexIndirect:
127 --it;
128 break;
129
130 default:
131 UNREACHABLE();
132 break;
133 }
134
135 currentNode = asBinary->getLeft();
136 }
137
138 currentNode = node;
139
140 while (currentNode->getAsBinaryNode())
141 {
142 TIntermBinary *asBinary = currentNode->getAsBinaryNode();
143
144 switch (asBinary->getOp())
145 {
146 case EOpIndexDirectStruct:
147 break;
148
149 case EOpIndexDirect:
150 case EOpIndexIndirect:
151 {
152 TIntermBinary *multiply =
153 new TIntermBinary(EOpMul, CreateIndexNode(static_cast<int>(*it++)),
154 asBinary->getRight()->deepCopy());
155 result = new TIntermBinary(EOpAdd, result, multiply);
156 break;
157 }
158
159 default:
160 UNREACHABLE();
161 break;
162 }
163
164 currentNode = asBinary->getLeft();
165 }
166
167 return result;
168}

170// Structures for keeping track of function instantiations.
171
172// An instantiation is keyed by the flattened sizes of the sampler arrays.
173typedef std::vector<size_t> Instantiation;
174
175struct InstantiationHash
176{
177 size_t operator()(const Instantiation &v) const noexcept
178 {
179 std::hash<size_t> hasher;
180 size_t seed = 0;
181 for (size_t x : v)
182 {
183 seed ^= hasher(x) + 0x9e3779b9 + (seed << 6) + (seed >> 2);
184 }
185 return seed;
186 }
187};
188
189// Map from each function to a "set" of instantiations.
190// We store a TFunction for each instantiation as its value.
191typedef std::map<ImmutableString, std::unordered_map<Instantiation, TFunction *, InstantiationHash>>
192 FunctionInstantiations;
193
194typedef std::unordered_map<const TFunction *, const TFunction *> FunctionMap;
195
196// Generates a new function from the given function using the given
197// instantiation; generatedInstantiations can be null.
198TFunction *GenerateFunctionFromArguments(const TFunction *function,
199 const TIntermSequence *arguments,
200 TSymbolTable *symbolTable,
201 FunctionInstantiations *functionInstantiations,
202 FunctionMap *functionMap,
203 const FunctionInstantiations *generatedInstantiations)
204{
205 // Collect sizes of array arguments.
206 Instantiation instantiation;
207 for (TIntermNode *node : *arguments)
208 {
209 const TType &type = node->getAsTyped()->getType();
210 if (type.isArray() && type.isSampler())
211 {
212 ASSERT(type.getNumArraySizes() == 1);
213 instantiation.push_back(type.getArraySizes()[0]);
214 }
215 }
216
217 if (generatedInstantiations)
218 {
219 auto it1 = generatedInstantiations->find(function->name());
220 if (it1 != generatedInstantiations->end())
221 {
222 const auto &map = it1->second;
223 auto it2 = map.find(instantiation);
224 if (it2 != map.end())
225 {
226 return it2->second;
227 }
228 }
229 }
230
231 TFunction **newFunction = &(*functionInstantiations)[function->name()][instantiation];
232
233 if (!*newFunction)
234 {
235 *newFunction =
236 new TFunction(symbolTable, kEmptyImmutableString, SymbolType::AngleInternal,
237 &function->getReturnType(), function->isKnownToNotHaveSideEffects());
238 (*functionMap)[*newFunction] = function;
239 // Insert parameters from updated function.
240 TFunction *updatedFunction = symbolTable->findUserDefinedFunction(function->name());
241 size_t paramCount = updatedFunction->getParamCount();
242 auto it = instantiation.begin();
243 for (size_t paramIndex = 0; paramIndex < paramCount; ++paramIndex)
244 {
245 const TVariable *param = updatedFunction->getParam(paramIndex);
246 const TType &paramType = param->getType();
247 if (paramType.isArray() && paramType.isSampler())
248 {
249 TType *replacementType = new TType(paramType);
250 size_t arraySize = *it++;
251 replacementType->setArraySize(0, static_cast<unsigned int>(arraySize));
252 param =
253 new TVariable(symbolTable, param->name(), replacementType, param->symbolType());
254 }
255 (*newFunction)->addParameter(param);
256 }
257 }
258 return *newFunction;
259}
260
261class ArrayTraverser
262{
263 public:
264 ArrayTraverser() { mCumulativeArraySizeStack.push_back(1); }
265
266 void enterArray(const TType &arrayType)
267 {
268 if (!arrayType.isArray())
269 return;
270 size_t currentArraySize = mCumulativeArraySizeStack.back();
271 const TSpan<const unsigned int> &arraySizes = arrayType.getArraySizes();
272 for (auto it = arraySizes.rbegin(); it != arraySizes.rend(); ++it)
273 {
274 unsigned int arraySize = *it;
275 currentArraySize *= arraySize;
276 mArraySizeStack.push_back(arraySize);
277 mCumulativeArraySizeStack.push_back(currentArraySize);
278 }
279 }
280
281 void exitArray(const TType &arrayType)
282 {
283 if (!arrayType.isArray())
284 return;
285 mArraySizeStack.resize(mArraySizeStack.size() - arrayType.getNumArraySizes());
286 mCumulativeArraySizeStack.resize(mCumulativeArraySizeStack.size() -
287 arrayType.getNumArraySizes());
288 }
289
290 protected:
291 std::vector<size_t> mArraySizeStack;
292 // The first element is 1; each successive element is the previous
293 // multiplied by the size of the next nested array in the current sampler.
294 // For example, with sampler2D foo[3][6], we would have {1, 3, 18}.
295 std::vector<size_t> mCumulativeArraySizeStack;
296};
297
298struct VariableExtraData
299{
300 // The value consists of strides, starting from the outermost array.
301 // For example, with sampler2D foo[3][6], we would have {1, 6, 18}.
302 std::unordered_map<const TVariable *, std::vector<size_t>> arrayStrideMap;
303 // For each generated array parameter, holds the offset parameter.
304 std::unordered_map<const TVariable *, const TVariable *> paramOffsetMap;
305};
306
307class Traverser final : public TIntermTraverser, public ArrayTraverser
308{
309 public:
310 explicit Traverser(TSymbolTable *symbolTable)
311 : TIntermTraverser(true, false, true, symbolTable), mRemovedUniformsCount(0)
312 {
313 mSymbolTable->push();
314 }
315
316 ~Traverser() override { mSymbolTable->pop(); }
317
318 int removedUniformsCount() const { return mRemovedUniformsCount; }
319
320 // Each struct sampler declaration is stripped of its samplers. New uniforms are added for each
321 // stripped struct sampler. Flattens all arrays, including default uniforms.
322 bool visitDeclaration(Visit visit, TIntermDeclaration *decl) override
323 {
324 if (visit != PreVisit)
325 return true;
326
327 if (!mInGlobalScope)
328 {
329 return true;
330 }
331
332 const TIntermSequence &sequence = *(decl->getSequence());
333 TIntermTyped *declarator = sequence.front()->getAsTyped();
334 const TType &type = declarator->getType();
335
336 if (type.isStructureContainingSamplers())
337 {
338 TIntermSequence *newSequence = new TIntermSequence;
339
340 if (type.isStructSpecifier())
341 {
342 stripStructSpecifierSamplers(type.getStruct(), newSequence);
343 }
344 else
345 {
346 TIntermSymbol *asSymbol = declarator->getAsSymbolNode();
347 ASSERT(asSymbol);
348 const TVariable &variable = asSymbol->variable();
349 ASSERT(variable.symbolType() != SymbolType::Empty);
350 extractStructSamplerUniforms(decl, variable, type.getStruct(), newSequence);
351 }
352
353 mMultiReplacements.emplace_back(getParentNode()->getAsBlock(), decl, *newSequence);
354 }
355
356 if ((type.isSampler() || type.isImage()) && type.isArray())
357 {
358 TIntermSequence *newSequence = new TIntermSequence;
359 TIntermSymbol *asSymbol = declarator->getAsSymbolNode();
360 ASSERT(asSymbol);
361 const TVariable &variable = asSymbol->variable();
362 ASSERT(variable.symbolType() != SymbolType::Empty);
363 extractSampler(variable.name(), variable.symbolType(), variable.getType(), newSequence,
364 0);
365 mMultiReplacements.emplace_back(getParentNode()->getAsBlock(), decl, *newSequence);
366 }
367
368 return true;
369 }
370
371 // Each struct sampler reference is replaced with a reference to the new extracted sampler.
372 bool visitBinary(Visit visit, TIntermBinary *node) override
373 {
374 if (visit != PreVisit)
375 return true;
376 // If the node isn't a sampler and it isn't an image or if this isn't the outermost
377 // access, continue.
378 if ((!node->getType().isSampler() && !node->getType().isImage()) ||
379 node->getType().isArray())
380 {
381 return true;
382 }
383
384 if (node->getOp() == EOpIndexDirect || node->getOp() == EOpIndexIndirect ||
385 node->getOp() == EOpIndexDirectStruct)
386 {
387 ImmutableString newName = GetStructSamplerNameFromTypedNode(node);
388 const TVariable *samplerReplacement =
389 static_cast<const TVariable *>(mSymbolTable->findUserDefined(newName));
390 ASSERT(samplerReplacement);
391
392 TIntermTyped *replacement = new TIntermSymbol(samplerReplacement);
393
394 if (replacement->isArray())
395 {
396 // Add in an indirect index if contained in an array
397 const auto &strides = mVariableExtraData.arrayStrideMap[samplerReplacement];
398 ASSERT(!strides.empty());
399 if (strides.size() > 1)
400 {
401 auto it = mVariableExtraData.paramOffsetMap.find(samplerReplacement);
402
403 TIntermTyped *offset =
404 it == mVariableExtraData.paramOffsetMap.end()
405 ? static_cast<TIntermTyped *>(CreateIndexNode(0))
406 : static_cast<TIntermTyped *>(new TIntermSymbol(it->second));
407
408 TIntermTyped *index = GetIndexExpressionFromTypedNode(node, strides, offset);
409 replacement = new TIntermBinary(EOpIndexIndirect, replacement, index);
410 }
411 }
412
413 queueReplacement(replacement, OriginalNode::IS_DROPPED);
414 return true;
415 }
416
417 return true;
418 }
419
420 // In we are passing references to structs containing samplers we must new additional
421 // arguments. For each extracted struct sampler a new argument is added. This chains to nested
422 // structs.
423 void visitFunctionPrototype(TIntermFunctionPrototype *node) override
424 {
425 const TFunction *function = node->getFunction();
426
427 if (!function->hasSamplerInStructOrArrayParams())
428 {
429 return;
430 }
431
432 const TSymbol *foundFunction = mSymbolTable->findUserDefined(function->name());
433 if (foundFunction)
434 {
435 ASSERT(foundFunction->isFunction());
436 function = static_cast<const TFunction *>(foundFunction);
437 }
438 else
439 {
440 TFunction *newFunction = createStructSamplerFunction(function);
441 mSymbolTable->declareUserDefinedFunction(newFunction, true);
442 function = newFunction;
443 }
444
445 ASSERT(!function->hasSamplerInStructOrArrayOfArrayParams());
446 TIntermFunctionPrototype *newProto = new TIntermFunctionPrototype(function);
447 queueReplacement(newProto, OriginalNode::IS_DROPPED);
448 }
449
450 // We insert a new scope for each function definition so we can track the new parameters.
451 bool visitFunctionDefinition(Visit visit, TIntermFunctionDefinition *node) override
452 {
453 if (visit == PreVisit)
454 {
455 mSymbolTable->push();
456 }
457 else
458 {
459 ASSERT(visit == PostVisit);
460 mSymbolTable->pop();
461 }
462 return true;
463 }
464
465 // For function call nodes we pass references to the extracted struct samplers in that scope.
466 bool visitAggregate(Visit visit, TIntermAggregate *node) override
467 {
468 if (visit != PreVisit)
469 return true;
470
471 if (!node->isFunctionCall())
472 return true;
473
474 const TFunction *function = node->getFunction();
475 if (!function->hasSamplerInStructOrArrayParams())
476 return true;
477
478 ASSERT(node->getOp() == EOpCallFunctionInAST);
479 TIntermSequence *newArguments = getStructSamplerArguments(function, node->getSequence());
480
481 TFunction *newFunction = GenerateFunctionFromArguments(
482 function, newArguments, mSymbolTable, &mFunctionInstantiations, &mFunctionMap, nullptr);
483
484 TIntermAggregate *newCall =
485 TIntermAggregate::CreateFunctionCall(*newFunction, newArguments);
486 queueReplacement(newCall, OriginalNode::IS_DROPPED);
487 return true;
488 }
489
490 FunctionInstantiations *getFunctionInstantiations() { return &mFunctionInstantiations; }
491
492 std::unordered_map<const TFunction *, const TFunction *> *getFunctionMap()
493 {
494 return &mFunctionMap;
495 }

497 private:
498 // This returns the name of a struct sampler reference. References are always TIntermBinary.
499 static ImmutableString GetStructSamplerNameFromTypedNode(TIntermTyped *node)
500 {
501 std::string stringBuilder;
502
503 TIntermTyped *currentNode = node;
504 while (currentNode->getAsBinaryNode())
505 {
506 TIntermBinary *asBinary = currentNode->getAsBinaryNode();
507
508 switch (asBinary->getOp())
509 {
510 case EOpIndexDirectStruct:
511 {
512 stringBuilder.insert(0, asBinary->getIndexStructFieldName().data());
513 stringBuilder.insert(0, "_");
514 break;
515 }
516
517 case EOpIndexDirect:
518 case EOpIndexIndirect:
519 break;
520
521 default:
522 UNREACHABLE();
523 break;
524 }
525
526 currentNode = asBinary->getLeft();
527 }
528
529 const ImmutableString &variableName = currentNode->getAsSymbolNode()->variable().name();
530 stringBuilder.insert(0, variableName.data());
531
532 return stringBuilder;
533 }
534
535 // Removes all the struct samplers from a struct specifier.
536 void stripStructSpecifierSamplers(const TStructure *structure, TIntermSequence *newSequence)
537 {
538 TFieldList *newFieldList = new TFieldList;
539 ASSERT(structure->containsSamplers());
540
541 for (const TField *field : structure->fields())
542 {
543 const TType &fieldType = *field->type();
544 if (!fieldType.isSampler() && !isRemovedStructType(fieldType))
545 {
546 TType *newType = nullptr;
547
548 if (fieldType.isStructureContainingSamplers())
549 {
550 const TSymbol *structSymbol =
551 mSymbolTable->findUserDefined(fieldType.getStruct()->name());
552 ASSERT(structSymbol && structSymbol->isStruct());
553 const TStructure *fieldStruct = static_cast<const TStructure *>(structSymbol);
554 newType = new TType(fieldStruct, true);
555 if (fieldType.isArray())
556 {
557 newType->makeArrays(fieldType.getArraySizes());
558 }
559 }
560 else
561 {
562 newType = new TType(fieldType);
563 }
564
565 TField *newField =
566 new TField(newType, field->name(), field->line(), field->symbolType());
567 newFieldList->push_back(newField);
568 }
569 }
570
571 // Prune empty structs.
572 if (newFieldList->empty())
573 {
574 mRemovedStructs.insert(structure->name());
575 return;
576 }
577
578 TStructure *newStruct =
579 new TStructure(mSymbolTable, structure->name(), newFieldList, structure->symbolType());
580 TType *newStructType = new TType(newStruct, true);
581 TVariable *newStructVar =
582 new TVariable(mSymbolTable, kEmptyImmutableString, newStructType, SymbolType::Empty);
583 TIntermSymbol *newStructRef = new TIntermSymbol(newStructVar);
584
585 TIntermDeclaration *structDecl = new TIntermDeclaration;
586 structDecl->appendDeclarator(newStructRef);
587
588 newSequence->push_back(structDecl);
589
590 mSymbolTable->declare(newStruct);
591 }
592
593 // Returns true if the type is a struct that was removed because we extracted all the members.
594 bool isRemovedStructType(const TType &type) const
595 {
596 const TStructure *structure = type.getStruct();
597 return (structure && (mRemovedStructs.count(structure->name()) > 0));
598 }
599
600 // Removes samplers from struct uniforms. For each sampler removed also adds a new globally
601 // defined sampler uniform.
602 void extractStructSamplerUniforms(TIntermDeclaration *oldDeclaration,
603 const TVariable &variable,
604 const TStructure *structure,
605 TIntermSequence *newSequence)
606 {
607 ASSERT(structure->containsSamplers());
608
609 size_t nonSamplerCount = 0;
610
611 enterArray(variable.getType());
612
613 for (const TField *field : structure->fields())
614 {
615 nonSamplerCount +=
616 extractFieldSamplers(variable.name(), field, variable.getType(), newSequence);
617 }
618
619 if (nonSamplerCount > 0)
620 {
621 // Keep the old declaration around if it has other members.
622 newSequence->push_back(oldDeclaration);
623 }
624 else
625 {
626 mRemovedUniformsCount++;
627 }
628
629 exitArray(variable.getType());
630 }
631
632 // Extracts samplers from a field of a struct. Works with nested structs and arrays.
633 size_t extractFieldSamplers(const ImmutableString &prefix,
634 const TField *field,
635 const TType &containingType,
636 TIntermSequence *newSequence)
637 {
638 return extractFieldSamplersImpl(prefix, field, newSequence);
639 }
640
641 // Extracts samplers from a field of a struct. Works with nested structs and arrays.
642 size_t extractFieldSamplersImpl(const ImmutableString &prefix,
643 const TField *field,
644 TIntermSequence *newSequence)
645 {
646 size_t nonSamplerCount = 0;
647
648 const TType &fieldType = *field->type();
649 if (fieldType.isSampler() || fieldType.isStructureContainingSamplers())
650 {
651 ImmutableStringBuilder stringBuilder(prefix.length() + field->name().length() + 1);
652 stringBuilder << prefix << "_" << field->name();
653 ImmutableString newPrefix(stringBuilder);
654
655 if (fieldType.isSampler())
656 {
657 extractSampler(newPrefix, SymbolType::AngleInternal, fieldType, newSequence, 0);
658 }
659 else
660 {
661 enterArray(fieldType);
662 const TStructure *structure = fieldType.getStruct();
663 for (const TField *nestedField : structure->fields())
664 {
665 nonSamplerCount +=
666 extractFieldSamplers(newPrefix, nestedField, fieldType, newSequence);
667 }
668 exitArray(fieldType);
669 }
670 }
671 else
672 {
673 nonSamplerCount++;
674 }
675
676 return nonSamplerCount;
677 }
678
679 // Extracts a sampler from a struct. Declares the new extracted sampler.
680 void extractSampler(const ImmutableString &newName,
681 SymbolType symbolType,
682 const TType &fieldType,
683 TIntermSequence *newSequence,
684 size_t arrayLevel)
685 {
686 enterArray(fieldType);
687
688 TType *newType = new TType(fieldType);
689 while (newType->isArray())
690 {
691 newType->toArrayElementType();
692 }
693 if (!mArraySizeStack.empty())
694 {
695 newType->makeArray(static_cast<unsigned int>(mCumulativeArraySizeStack.back()));
696 }
697 newType->setQualifier(EvqUniform);
698 TVariable *newVariable = new TVariable(mSymbolTable, newName, newType, symbolType);
699 TIntermSymbol *newRef = new TIntermSymbol(newVariable);
700
701 TIntermDeclaration *samplerDecl = new TIntermDeclaration;
702 samplerDecl->appendDeclarator(newRef);
703
704 newSequence->push_back(samplerDecl);
705
706 // TODO(syoussefi): Use a SymbolType::Empty name instead of generating a name as currently
707 // done. There is no guarantee that these generated names cannot clash. Create a mapping
708 // from the previous name to the name assigned to the SymbolType::Empty variable so
709 // ShaderVariable::mappedName can be updated post-transformation.
710 // http://anglebug.com/4301
711 if (symbolType == SymbolType::AngleInternal)
712 {
713 mSymbolTable->declareInternal(newVariable);
714 }
715 else
716 {
717 mSymbolTable->declare(newVariable);
718 }
719
720 GenerateArrayStrides(mArraySizeStack, &mVariableExtraData.arrayStrideMap[newVariable]);
721
722 exitArray(fieldType);
723 }
724
725 // Returns the chained name of a sampler uniform field.
726 static ImmutableString GetFieldName(const ImmutableString &paramName, const TField *field)
727 {
728 ImmutableStringBuilder nameBuilder(paramName.length() + 1 + field->name().length());
729 nameBuilder << paramName << "_";
730 nameBuilder << field->name();
731
732 return nameBuilder;
733 }

735 // A pattern that visits every parameter of a function call. Uses different handlers for struct
736 // parameters, struct sampler parameters, and non-struct parameters.
737 class StructSamplerFunctionVisitor : angle::NonCopyable, public ArrayTraverser
738 {
739 public:
740 StructSamplerFunctionVisitor() = default;
741 virtual ~StructSamplerFunctionVisitor() = default;
742
743 virtual void traverse(const TFunction *function)
744 {
745 size_t paramCount = function->getParamCount();
746
747 for (size_t paramIndex = 0; paramIndex < paramCount; ++paramIndex)
748 {
749 const TVariable *param = function->getParam(paramIndex);
750 const TType &paramType = param->getType();
751
752 if (paramType.isStructureContainingSamplers())
753 {
754 const ImmutableString &baseName = getNameFromIndex(function, paramIndex);
755 if (traverseStructContainingSamplers(baseName, paramType, paramIndex))
756 {
757 visitStructParam(function, paramIndex);
758 }
759 }
760 else if (paramType.isArray() && paramType.isSampler())
761 {
762 const ImmutableString &paramName = getNameFromIndex(function, paramIndex);
763 traverseLeafSampler(paramName, paramType, paramIndex);
764 }
765 else
766 {
767 visitNonStructParam(function, paramIndex);
768 }
769 }
770 }
771
772 virtual ImmutableString getNameFromIndex(const TFunction *function, size_t paramIndex) = 0;
773 // Also includes samplers in arrays of arrays.
774 virtual void visitSamplerInStructParam(const ImmutableString &name,
775 const TType *type,
776 size_t paramIndex) = 0;
777 virtual void visitStructParam(const TFunction *function, size_t paramIndex) = 0;
778 virtual void visitNonStructParam(const TFunction *function, size_t paramIndex) = 0;
779
780 private:
781 bool traverseStructContainingSamplers(const ImmutableString &baseName,
782 const TType &structType,
783 size_t paramIndex)
784 {
785 bool hasNonSamplerFields = false;
786 const TStructure *structure = structType.getStruct();
787 enterArray(structType);
788 for (const TField *field : structure->fields())
789 {
790 if (field->type()->isStructureContainingSamplers() || field->type()->isSampler())
791 {
792 if (traverseSamplerInStruct(baseName, structType, field, paramIndex))
793 {
794 hasNonSamplerFields = true;
795 }
796 }
797 else
798 {
799 hasNonSamplerFields = true;
800 }
801 }
802 exitArray(structType);
803 return hasNonSamplerFields;
804 }
805
806 bool traverseSamplerInStruct(const ImmutableString &baseName,
807 const TType &baseType,
808 const TField *field,
809 size_t paramIndex)
810 {
811 bool hasNonSamplerParams = false;
812
813 if (field->type()->isStructureContainingSamplers())
814 {
815 ImmutableString name = GetFieldName(baseName, field);
816 hasNonSamplerParams =
817 traverseStructContainingSamplers(name, *field->type(), paramIndex);
818 }
819 else
820 {
821 ASSERT(field->type()->isSampler());
822 ImmutableString name = GetFieldName(baseName, field);
823 traverseLeafSampler(name, *field->type(), paramIndex);
824 }
825
826 return hasNonSamplerParams;
827 }
828
829 void traverseLeafSampler(const ImmutableString &samplerName,
830 const TType &samplerType,
831 size_t paramIndex)
832 {
833 enterArray(samplerType);
834 visitSamplerInStructParam(samplerName, &samplerType, paramIndex);
835 exitArray(samplerType);
836 return;
837 }
838 };
839
840 // A visitor that replaces functions with struct sampler references. The struct sampler
841 // references are expanded to include new fields for the structs.
842 class CreateStructSamplerFunctionVisitor final : public StructSamplerFunctionVisitor
843 {
844 public:
845 CreateStructSamplerFunctionVisitor(TSymbolTable *symbolTable, VariableExtraData *extraData)
846 : mSymbolTable(symbolTable), mNewFunction(nullptr), mExtraData(extraData)
847 {}
848
849 ImmutableString getNameFromIndex(const TFunction *function, size_t paramIndex) override
850 {
851 const TVariable *param = function->getParam(paramIndex);
852 return param->name();
853 }
854
855 void traverse(const TFunction *function) override
856 {
857 mNewFunction =
858 new TFunction(mSymbolTable, function->name(), function->symbolType(),
859 &function->getReturnType(), function->isKnownToNotHaveSideEffects());
860
861 StructSamplerFunctionVisitor::traverse(function);
862 }
863
864 void visitSamplerInStructParam(const ImmutableString &name,
865 const TType *type,
866 size_t paramIndex) override
867 {
868 if (mArraySizeStack.size() > 0)
869 {
870 TType *newType = new TType(*type);
871 newType->toArrayBaseType();
872 newType->makeArray(static_cast<unsigned int>(mCumulativeArraySizeStack.back()));
873 type = newType;
874 }
875 TVariable *fieldSampler =
876 new TVariable(mSymbolTable, name, type, SymbolType::AngleInternal);
877 mNewFunction->addParameter(fieldSampler);
878 mSymbolTable->declareInternal(fieldSampler);
879 if (mArraySizeStack.size() > 0)
880 {
881 // Also declare an offset parameter.
882 const TType *intType = StaticType::GetBasic<EbtInt>();
883 TVariable *samplerOffset = new TVariable(mSymbolTable, kEmptyImmutableString,
884 intType, SymbolType::AngleInternal);
885 mNewFunction->addParameter(samplerOffset);
886 GenerateArrayStrides(mArraySizeStack, &mExtraData->arrayStrideMap[fieldSampler]);
887 mExtraData->paramOffsetMap[fieldSampler] = samplerOffset;
888 }
889 }
890
891 void visitStructParam(const TFunction *function, size_t paramIndex) override
892 {
893 const TVariable *param = function->getParam(paramIndex);
894 TType *structType = GetStructSamplerParameterType(mSymbolTable, *param);
895 TVariable *newParam =
896 new TVariable(mSymbolTable, param->name(), structType, param->symbolType());
897 mNewFunction->addParameter(newParam);
898 }
899
900 void visitNonStructParam(const TFunction *function, size_t paramIndex) override
901 {
902 const TVariable *param = function->getParam(paramIndex);
903 mNewFunction->addParameter(param);
904 }
905
906 TFunction *getNewFunction() const { return mNewFunction; }
907
908 private:
909 TSymbolTable *mSymbolTable;
910 TFunction *mNewFunction;
911 VariableExtraData *mExtraData;
912 };
913
914 TFunction *createStructSamplerFunction(const TFunction *function)
915 {
916 CreateStructSamplerFunctionVisitor visitor(mSymbolTable, &mVariableExtraData);
917 visitor.traverse(function);
918 return visitor.getNewFunction();
919 }
920
921 // A visitor that replaces function calls with expanded struct sampler parameters.
922 class GetSamplerArgumentsVisitor final : public StructSamplerFunctionVisitor
923 {
924 public:
925 GetSamplerArgumentsVisitor(TSymbolTable *symbolTable,
926 const TIntermSequence *arguments,
927 VariableExtraData *extraData)
928 : mSymbolTable(symbolTable),
929 mArguments(arguments),
930 mNewArguments(new TIntermSequence),
931 mExtraData(extraData)
932 {}
933
934 ImmutableString getNameFromIndex(const TFunction *function, size_t paramIndex) override
935 {
936 TIntermTyped *argument = (*mArguments)[paramIndex]->getAsTyped();
937 return GetStructSamplerNameFromTypedNode(argument);
938 }
939
940 void visitSamplerInStructParam(const ImmutableString &name,
941 const TType *type,
942 size_t paramIndex) override
943 {
944 const TVariable *argSampler =
945 static_cast<const TVariable *>(mSymbolTable->findUserDefined(name));
946 ASSERT(argSampler);
947
948 TIntermTyped *argument = (*mArguments)[paramIndex]->getAsTyped();
949
950 auto it = mExtraData->paramOffsetMap.find(argSampler);
951 TIntermTyped *argOffset =
952 it == mExtraData->paramOffsetMap.end()
953 ? static_cast<TIntermTyped *>(CreateIndexNode(0))
954 : static_cast<TIntermTyped *>(new TIntermSymbol(it->second));
955
956 TIntermTyped *finalOffset = GetIndexExpressionFromTypedNode(
957 argument, mExtraData->arrayStrideMap[argSampler], argOffset);
958
959 TIntermSymbol *argSymbol = new TIntermSymbol(argSampler);
960
961 // If we have a regular sampler inside a struct (possibly an array
962 // of structs), handle this case separately.
963 if (!type->isArray() && mArraySizeStack.size() == 0)
964 {
965 if (argSampler->getType().isArray())
966 {
967 TIntermTyped *argIndex =
968 new TIntermBinary(EOpIndexIndirect, argSymbol, finalOffset);
969 mNewArguments->push_back(argIndex);
970 }
971 else
972 {
973 mNewArguments->push_back(argSymbol);
974 }
975 return;
976 }
977
978 mNewArguments->push_back(argSymbol);
979
980 mNewArguments->push_back(finalOffset);
981 // If array, we need to calculate the offset based on what indices
982 // are present in the argument.
983 }
984
985 void visitStructParam(const TFunction *function, size_t paramIndex) override
986 {
987 // The tree structure of the parameter is modified to point to the new type. This leaves
988 // the tree in a consistent state.
989 TIntermTyped *argument = (*mArguments)[paramIndex]->getAsTyped();
990 TIntermTyped *replacement = ReplaceTypeOfTypedStructNode(argument, mSymbolTable);
991 mNewArguments->push_back(replacement);
992 }
993
994 void visitNonStructParam(const TFunction *function, size_t paramIndex) override
995 {
996 TIntermTyped *argument = (*mArguments)[paramIndex]->getAsTyped();
997 mNewArguments->push_back(argument);
998 }
999
1000 TIntermSequence *getNewArguments() const { return mNewArguments; }
1001
1002 private:
1003 TSymbolTable *mSymbolTable;
1004 const TIntermSequence *mArguments;
1005 TIntermSequence *mNewArguments;
1006 VariableExtraData *mExtraData;
1007 };
1008
1009 TIntermSequence *getStructSamplerArguments(const TFunction *function,
1010 const TIntermSequence *arguments)
1011 {
1012 GetSamplerArgumentsVisitor visitor(mSymbolTable, arguments, &mVariableExtraData);
1013 visitor.traverse(function);
1014 return visitor.getNewArguments();
1015 }
1016
1017 int mRemovedUniformsCount;
1018 std::set<ImmutableString> mRemovedStructs;
1019 FunctionInstantiations mFunctionInstantiations;
1020 FunctionMap mFunctionMap;
1021 VariableExtraData mVariableExtraData;
1022};

1024class MonomorphizeTraverser final : public TIntermTraverser
1025{
1026 public:
1027 typedef std::unordered_map<const TVariable *, const TVariable *> VariableReplacementMap;
1028
1029 explicit MonomorphizeTraverser(
1030 TCompiler *compiler,
1031 TSymbolTable *symbolTable,
1032 FunctionInstantiations *functionInstantiations,
1033 std::unordered_map<const TFunction *, const TFunction *> *functionMap)
1034 : TIntermTraverser(true, false, true, symbolTable),
1035 mFunctionInstantiations(*functionInstantiations),
1036 mFunctionMap(functionMap),
1037 mCompiler(compiler),
1038 mSubpassesSucceeded(true)
1039 {}
1040
1041 void switchToPending()
1042 {
1043 mFunctionInstantiations.clear();
1044 mFunctionInstantiations.swap(mPendingInstantiations);
1045 }
1046
1047 bool hasPending()
1048 {
1049 if (mPendingInstantiations.empty())
1050 return false;
1051 for (auto &entry : mPendingInstantiations)
1052 {
1053 if (!entry.second.empty())
1054 {
1055 return true;
1056 }
1057 }
1058 return false;
1059 }
1060
1061 bool subpassesSucceeded() { return mSubpassesSucceeded; }
1062
1063 void visitFunctionPrototype(TIntermFunctionPrototype *node) override
1064 {
1065 mReplacementPrototypes.clear();
1066 const TFunction *function = node->getFunction();
1067
1068 auto &generatedMap = mGeneratedInstantiations[function->name()];
1069
1070 auto it = mFunctionInstantiations.find(function->name());
1071 if (it == mFunctionInstantiations.end())
1072 return;
1073 for (const auto &instantiation : it->second)
1074 {
1075 TFunction *replacementFunction = instantiation.second;
1076 mReplacementPrototypes.push_back(new TIntermFunctionPrototype(replacementFunction));
1077 generatedMap[instantiation.first] = replacementFunction;
1078 }
1079 if (!mInFunctionDefinition)
1080 {
1081 insertStatementsInParentBlock(mReplacementPrototypes);
1082 }
1083 }
1084
1085 bool visitFunctionDefinition(Visit visit, TIntermFunctionDefinition *node) override
1086 {
1087 mInFunctionDefinition = visit == PreVisit;
1088 if (visit != PostVisit)
1089 return true;
1090 TIntermSequence replacements;
1091 const TFunction *function = node->getFunction();
1092 size_t numParameters = function->getParamCount();
1093
1094 for (TIntermNode *replacementNode : mReplacementPrototypes)
1095 {
1096 TIntermFunctionPrototype *replacementPrototype =
1097 replacementNode->getAsFunctionPrototypeNode();
1098 const TFunction *replacementFunction = replacementPrototype->getFunction();
1099
1100 // Replace function parameters with correct array sizes.
1101 VariableReplacementMap variableReplacementMap;
1102 ASSERT(replacementPrototype->getFunction()->getParamCount() == numParameters);
1103 for (size_t i = 0; i < numParameters; i++)
1104 {
1105 const TVariable *origParam = function->getParam(i);
1106 const TVariable *newParam = replacementFunction->getParam(i);
1107 if (origParam != newParam)
1108 {
1109 variableReplacementMap[origParam] = newParam;
1110 }
1111 }
1112
1113 TIntermBlock *body = node->getBody()->deepCopy();
1114 ReplaceVariablesTraverser replaceVariables(mSymbolTable, &variableReplacementMap);
1115 body->traverse(&replaceVariables);
1116 mSubpassesSucceeded &= replaceVariables.updateTree(mCompiler, body);
1117 CollectNewInstantiationsTraverser collectNewInstantiations(
1118 mSymbolTable, &mPendingInstantiations, &mGeneratedInstantiations, mFunctionMap);
1119 body->traverse(&collectNewInstantiations);
1120 mSubpassesSucceeded &= collectNewInstantiations.updateTree(mCompiler, body);
1121 replacements.push_back(new TIntermFunctionDefinition(replacementPrototype, body));
1122 }
1123 insertStatementsInParentBlock(replacements);
1124 return true;
1125 }
1126
1127 private:
1128 bool mInFunctionDefinition;
1129 FunctionInstantiations mFunctionInstantiations;
1130 // Set of already-generated instantiations.
1131 FunctionInstantiations mGeneratedInstantiations;
1132 // New instantiations caused by other instantiations.
1133 FunctionInstantiations mPendingInstantiations;
1134 std::unordered_map<const TFunction *, const TFunction *> *mFunctionMap;
1135 TIntermSequence mReplacementPrototypes;
1136 TCompiler *mCompiler;
1137 bool mSubpassesSucceeded;
1138
1139 class ReplaceVariablesTraverser : public TIntermTraverser
1140 {
1141 public:
1142 explicit ReplaceVariablesTraverser(TSymbolTable *symbolTable,
1143 VariableReplacementMap *variableReplacementMap)
1144 : TIntermTraverser(true, false, false, symbolTable),
1145 mVariableReplacementMap(variableReplacementMap)
1146 {}
1147
1148 void visitSymbol(TIntermSymbol *node) override
1149 {
1150 const TVariable *variable = &node->variable();
1151 auto it = mVariableReplacementMap->find(variable);
1152 if (it != mVariableReplacementMap->end())
1153 {
1154 queueReplacement(new TIntermSymbol(it->second), OriginalNode::IS_DROPPED);
1155 }
1156 }
1157
1158 private:
1159 VariableReplacementMap *mVariableReplacementMap;
1160 };
1161
1162 class CollectNewInstantiationsTraverser : public TIntermTraverser
1163 {
1164 public:
1165 explicit CollectNewInstantiationsTraverser(
1166 TSymbolTable *symbolTable,
1167 FunctionInstantiations *pendingInstantiations,
1168 FunctionInstantiations *generatedInstantiations,
1169 std::unordered_map<const TFunction *, const TFunction *> *functionMap)
1170 : TIntermTraverser(true, false, false, symbolTable),
1171 mPendingInstantiations(pendingInstantiations),
1172 mGeneratedInstantiations(generatedInstantiations),
1173 mFunctionMap(functionMap)
1174 {}
1175
1176 bool visitAggregate(Visit visit, TIntermAggregate *node) override
1177 {
1178 if (!node->isFunctionCall())
1179 return true;
1180 const TFunction *function = node->getFunction();
1181 const TFunction *oldFunction;
1182 {
1183 auto it = mFunctionMap->find(function);
1184 if (it == mFunctionMap->end())
1185 return true;
1186 oldFunction = it->second;
1187 }
1188 ASSERT(node->getOp() == EOpCallFunctionInAST);
1189 TIntermSequence *arguments = node->getSequence();
1190 TFunction *newFunction = GenerateFunctionFromArguments(
1191 oldFunction, arguments, mSymbolTable, mPendingInstantiations, mFunctionMap,
1192 mGeneratedInstantiations);
1193 queueReplacement(TIntermAggregate::CreateFunctionCall(*newFunction, arguments),
1194 OriginalNode::IS_DROPPED);
1195 return true;
1196 }
1197
1198 private:
1199 FunctionInstantiations *mPendingInstantiations;
1200 FunctionInstantiations *mGeneratedInstantiations;
1201 std::unordered_map<const TFunction *, const TFunction *> *mFunctionMap;
1202 };
1203};
1204} // anonymous namespace
1205
1206bool RewriteStructSamplers(TCompiler *compiler,
1207 TIntermBlock *root,
1208 TSymbolTable *symbolTable,
1209 int *removedUniformsCountOut)
1210{
1211 Traverser rewriteStructSamplers(symbolTable);
1212 root->traverse(&rewriteStructSamplers);
1213 if (!rewriteStructSamplers.updateTree(compiler, root))
1214 {
1215 return false;
1216 }
1217 *removedUniformsCountOut = rewriteStructSamplers.removedUniformsCount();
1218
1219 if (rewriteStructSamplers.getFunctionInstantiations()->empty())
1220 {
1221 return true;
1222 }
1223
1224 MonomorphizeTraverser monomorphizeFunctions(compiler, symbolTable,
1225 rewriteStructSamplers.getFunctionInstantiations(),
1226 rewriteStructSamplers.getFunctionMap());
1227 root->traverse(&monomorphizeFunctions);
1228 if (!monomorphizeFunctions.subpassesSucceeded())
1229 {
1230 return false;
1231 }
1232 if (!monomorphizeFunctions.updateTree(compiler, root))
1233 {
1234 return false;
1235 }
1236
1237 // Generate instantiations caused by other instantiations.
1238 while (monomorphizeFunctions.hasPending())
1239 {
1240 monomorphizeFunctions.switchToPending();
1241 root->traverse(&monomorphizeFunctions);
1242 if (!monomorphizeFunctions.subpassesSucceeded())
1243 {
1244 return false;
1245 }
1246 if (!monomorphizeFunctions.updateTree(compiler, root))
1247 {
1248 return false;
1249 }
1250 }
1251
1252 return true;
1253}
